(10,'<div style=\"float:left;\">\n<inputbox>\ntype=create \nbreak=no \nbuttonlabel=Create new article with this title  \n</inputbox>\n</div><div style=\"clear:left;\"></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
(11,'\n\n== Parsifal Cheat Sheet ==\n\n== Editor ==\n\nIf the editor frame window is focused,\nadjust the font size of the editor\nusing <code>Cmd +</code> or <code>Cmd -</code> \nwithout resizing the rest of the browser.\n\n\n=== Attributes ===\n\n==== Collapse ====\n\n==== Continuation ====\nSituation: We want to split TeX text into several smaller portions.\nAdvantages of this are:\n* Faster preview\n* Smaller unit of error and unit of editing\n* Seperate edit link\n\nFor the presentation, there can be several scenarios:\n* Separation: We want a bit of markup which lets the reader see that there are two\ndifferent portions of text. \n* Continuation: We do not want to indicate this separation into two different portions of text. The second portion should be a seamless continuation of the\nfirst text. Nevertheless there should be a possibility for the reader to recognize the two parts and to invoke edit links and similar actions for the\ntwo parts.\n\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
(12,'\n\n== Dante Links ==\n* Provides a possibility to add attributes to links.\n* Ensures that links (A-elements) with target \n** _window open in a separate window, next to the browser, of similar size\n** _side open in an 800x800 window left on the screen.\n\n* Provide markup for external links  which open in a separate window \n[https://www.w3c.org W3C \\w]\nas opposed to [https://www.w3c.org W3C]\n\n\n\n== Dante Tree ==\n\n* A shift-click on to a Category link opens the category window as seperate popup window in small size and on the left of the screen. This proved helpful for quick deploy of a category window as an overview.\n\n* A shift-click on a link into a portal heading opens an edit window for that portal content.\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
(13,'\n== Configuring the Sidebar ==\n\n* Main Sidebar File: [[MediaWiki:Sidebar]]\n* Sidebar Tree Files:\n** [[MediaWiki:Sidebar/Areas]]\n** [[MediaWiki:Sidebar/Social]]\n* Sidebar Category Definition: [[MediaWiki:Sidebar/Categories]]\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
(14,'asdaa\n\n== Titel ==\n\n<amsmath n=\"Myname\">o f t  h is   d\n   qweq\n\\xcx\n\nRule of 14cm  \n\\hrule height 1px depth 1px width 14cm \\relax         \n\nRule  of 14.2cm  \n\\hrule height 1px depth 1px width 14.2cm \\relax\n\nRule of s 15cm\n\\hrule height 1px depth 1px width 15cm \\relax\n\nRule of 16cm\n\\hrule height 1px depth 1px width 16cm \\relax\n</amsmath>\n   \n<hide>\n\n== Part 2 ==\n<amsmath>\nb ja q q io qw qw   fje ssqa aa sj jhgjhg jhgssssssss\n</amsmath>\n\n</hide>\n\n== One ==\n<beamer b>\nHallo2345123 123 123 \nDas ist jakjh \n$a$=$b$ kjh  kjqh k jkl lkj j h iuaahh zh qwe asd u io\n</beamer>\n\n== Stuff ==\n<beamer b>\nThis is no w asdcvmmsd b weasdasd asd  qwe as d  qwe a sd qw e asd qwe asd qwe asd qwe asd qwe  asd qwe asd qwe asd qwe asd qwe asd beamer a sd\n</beamer>\n\n== Only ==\n\n<amsmath n=\"Myname\">J xust  a test</amsmath>\n\n== Titel Y ==\n\n<amsmath o-proof>\nEa iaaa  sdsa df ax sda   gg   n s\n</amsmath>\n\n<amsmath c-habanalop>Zwhc \nsdf sdf\nsdfsd f\nxxjj\nsdfsdf\nas\nsdfsdf\nsdfsdf\n\nsdfsdf\n\nsdfsdf\n\nsdfsdf\n\nsdfsdf\n\nsdfsdfgh\n\nsdfsdf\n\nsdfsdf\n\nsdfsdf\n\nsdfsdf\n\nsdfsdf\n\nsdfsdfsdf\n\nsdf\n\nsdfe i</amsmath>\n\n<amsmath c=\"Ha bA Na\">\nDrei \\url{https://www.ifi.ch}\n</amsmath>\n\n\n== Test; Style Attribute ==\n<amsmath style=\"border:10px solid green;\">\n921iihj kjh ujkWe6697 i m a sdf  ke a meas urement and  get a r esu lt  $\\omega$. We now assume we can talk of an object with the property $\\omega$. We cannota\nsay that the object is (or is in the state) $\\omega$ as this description might not be precise enough in the sense that the object\nmight have additional properties as well (The color red is an insufficient characterization of an object). We have the fantasy that\n</amsmath>\n\n\n\n\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
(15,'\n\n== Simple Highlight ==\n<syntaxhighlight>\nlet x = 7;\n</syntaxhighlight>\n\n== More Complex Highlight ==\nŌĆÄ<syntaxhighlight lang=\"python\">\ndef quick_sort(arr):\n	less = []\n	pivot_list = []\n	more = []\n	if len(arr) <= 1:\n		return arr\n	else:\n		pass\nŌĆÄ</syntaxhighlight>\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
(16,'\n\n\nWindow\n* [https://blog.fefe.de \\w]\n* [https://blog.fefe.de Fefe \\w]\n\n\nSide\n* [https://blog.fefe.de \\s]\n* [https://blog.fefe.de Fefe \\s]\n\n\n\'\'\'Example\'\'\'\n* <nowiki>[[Main Page || doub]]</nowiki>\n* [[Main Page || doub]] \n\n* <nowiki>[[Main Page \\| doub]]</nowiki>\n* [[Main Page \\| doub]]\n\n\n\'\'\'Example\'\'\'\n* <nowiki>[[Main Page ┬” style=color:green;]]</nowiki>\n* [[Main Page ┬” style=color:green;]]\n\n\'\'\'Example\'\'\'\n* <nowiki>[[Help:Demo for DanteLinks ┬” style=color:green;]]</nowiki>\n* [[Help:Demo for DanteLinks ┬” style=color:green;]]\n\n\'\'\'Example:\'\'\' Adding style attributes to an external link via broken pipe symbol\n* <nowiki>[https://blog.fefe.de Fefe ┬” style=color:green;]</nowiki> produces\n* [https://blog.fefe.de Fefe ┬” style=color:green;]\n\n\n\'\'\'Example:\'\'\' Adding target attribute _blank to an external link opens it in a new tab\n* <nowiki>[https://blog.fefe.de Fefe ┬” target=_blank ]</nowiki> produces:\n* [https://blog.fefe.de Fefe ┬” target=_blank ]\n\nFor use in sidebars only: There is a special class dexternal which can be used to append an external link symbol to link. In the sidebar links which otherwise are external will not show the symbol external. This is as we need query extensions for a number of links in the sidebar and this needs fullurl as parser and this causes the parser to understand the link as external in every case. Therefore we turned this thingie off in sidebar until we find a smart fix for this.\n\n[[Main Page]]\n\nAnd here [[Main Page]] some text [https://blog.fefe.de Fefe] to see the distances when\nrendering in text.\n\n\n== Requirements ==\n\n* We always want to see where a link goes (internal or external)\n* We always want to know where a link opens (same tab, new tab, new window)\n* We want to allow the user to open the link where he wants to (same tab, new tab, new window)\n* We want to force-open some links in specific modes (same tab, new tab, new window) when the user only clicks normally.\n\n== All Link Types ==\n\n<table>\n<tr><td>Internal</td><td><nowiki>[[Main Page]]</nowiki></td><td>[[Main Page]]</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Piped</td><td><nowiki>[[Main Page|Hauptseite]]</nowiki></td><td>[[Main Page|Hauptseite]]</td></tr>\n\n\n<tr><td>External numbered</td><td><nowiki>[https://blog.fefe.de]</nowiki></td><td>[https://blog.fefe.de]</td></tr>\n<tr><td>External text</td><td><nowiki>[https://blog.fefe.de Fefe]</nowiki></td><td>[https://blog.fefe.de Fefe]</td></tr>\n<tr><td>External bare</td><td><nowiki>https://blog.fefe.de</nowiki></td><td>https://blog.fefe.de</td></tr>\n\n\n</table>\n\n\n[[Main Page]]s\n\n[https://blog.fefe.de Fefe]\n\n\n[[Murundai\\w]]\n\n[https://blog.fefe.de Hurundai\\w]\n\n[[Pipetrick (computing)|Pipetrick]] \n\n\n\n\n[[:Category:Root]]\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
