(58,'\n\n== FAQ ==\n\n=== Why is this called DanteWiki? ===\nThe thought of writing done what one has understood dates\nback to Dante:\n\n\"O mente, che scrivesti ci├▓ chŌĆÖio vidi\" (Dante, Inferno II, 8)\n\n\"O Ged├żchtnis, das geschrieben, was ich erkannte\" (own translation)\n\nThis thought has also been described in a letter of \nNicolo Machiavelli to Francesco Vettori, florentinian\nambassador in Rome. \nWe cite it here according to Niccolo Machiavelli, Der F├╝rst. \nSuhrkamp Verlag, 2016:\n\n<poem>\nUnd weil Dante sagt, es gebe keine Wissenschaft ohne die Aufzeichnung dessen,\nwas man begriffen hat ŌĆō so habe ich das notiert, was ich bei dem Gespr├żch\nmit Ihnen als das Wesentliche festhielt, und ein kleines Werk ├╝ber F├╝rstent├╝mer\nverfa├¤t, worin ich mich so weit wie m├Čglich in die Gedanken ├╝ber dieses Thema\nvertiefe und er├Črtere, was Herrschaft ist, welche Arten es davon gib, wie man sie\nerwirbt und erh├żlt und warum man sie verliert.\n</poem>\n\nOr, for short:\n\n\"[E]s [gibt] keine Wissenschaft ohne die Aufzeichnung dessen, was\nman begriffen hat.\"\n\n\"There is no science without a record of what one has understood\" (own translation)\n\nThat\'s why I call this Wiki system a DanteWiki.\n\n=== What does the logo show? ===\nThe logo shows a painting made \nby Michelangelo Merisi da Caravaggio in 1607. It depicts Saint Jerome\nof Stridon, who is best known for his translations of the Bible into Latin. \nit here serves as the symbol of a scientist, philosopher and thinker.\nSaint Jerome is alone, remote from the distractions of the world,\nfocused alone on putting down his thoughts.\nThe skull on his table reminds us of the mortality of man and the\nvolatility of his thoughts.\nIt thus challenges us to write down our thoughts.\n\nThe logo thus reflexts my core motives when creating this system.\n\n=== What is the relation to MediaWiki? ===\nNone.\n\nI did not want to build this system completely from scratch.\nMediaWiki was the software which contained most of the necessary \nbase functionality and was open for further development \ndue to its open license model.\nI will try to keep DanteWiki as close to MediaWiki as possible\nto ease maintenence and bug fixing.\n\n=== What is the relation to WikiPedia? ===\nNone.\n\nWhile WikiPedia is a very interesting project, I do not\nsubscribe to the objectivist perspective on which it seems\nto be grounded. In particular - in my opinion - \nthe neutral point of view goal of WikiPedia cannot be achieved\nfor a number of linguistic reasons and should not\nbe aimed for due to a number of philosophic reasons.\n\nDanteWiki follows different goals and guidelines.','utf-8'),
