(106,'\nh\nhere is the link: [[Sniptest]]','utf-8'),
(107,'\n\n\n==== Perpetual Beta ====\nPerpetual beta is a general concept of web 2.0 in which a service is never considered\ncomplete or finished but permanently is in a preliminary or draft (i.e. beta) status.\nThis is inevitable in many web 2.0 services, as only during the construction of the system\na better understanding of the requirements emerges.\n\n\n==== Bootstrapped Development ====\nBootstrapped development is common in open knowledge management systems. The system itself is\nused for documenting the work with the system, as it is done on this page. Throughout this\nprocess the users and developers learn about their knowledge management needs.\n\n==== User Co-Development ====\nThe system is not developed by IT architects for users but by a user for the needs of the\nusers. Thus, the developers are typical representatives of the user community, which\navoids the usual distance between developers and users.\n\n\n\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
