(122,'Pages in this category are for testing and demo purposes only.\n[[Category:DanteInitialCustomize]]','utf-8'),
(123,'\n\n<pre>\nFile:Dblp.png\nFile:Example.svg\nFile:Flex.svg\nFile:T-diagram.svg\nFile:Compiler-abstraktion.svg\nFile:Compiler-und-interpreter.svg\n</pre>\n[[Category:DanteInitialCustomize]]','utf-8'),
(124,'\n\n<pre>\nFile:Dblp.png\nFile:Example.svg\nFile:Flex.svg\nFile:T-diagram.svg\nFile:Compiler-abstraktion.svg\nFile:Compiler-und-interpreter.svg\n</pre>','utf-8'),
(125,'\n\n<pre>\nFile:Dblp.png\nFile:Example.svg\nFile:Flex.svg\nFile:T-diagram.svg\nFile:Compiler-abstraktion.svg\nFile:Compiler-und-interpreter.svg\n</pre>\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
(126,'\n\n== FAQ ==\n\n=== Why is this called DanteWiki? ===\nThe thought of writing done what one has understood dates\nback to Dante:\n\n\"O mente, che scrivesti ci├▓ chŌĆÖio vidi\" (Dante, Inferno II, 8)\n\n\"O Ged├żchtnis, das geschrieben, was ich erkannte\" (own translation)\n\nThis thought has also been described in a letter of \nNicolo Machiavelli to Francesco Vettori, florentinian\nambassador in Rome. \nWe cite it here according to Niccolo Machiavelli, Der F├╝rst. \nSuhrkamp Verlag, 2016:\n\n<poem>\nUnd weil Dante sagt, es gebe keine Wissenschaft ohne die Aufzeichnung dessen,\nwas man begriffen hat ŌĆō so habe ich das notiert, was ich bei dem Gespr├żch\nmit Ihnen als das Wesentliche festhielt, und ein kleines Werk ├╝ber F├╝rstent├╝mer\nverfa├¤t, worin ich mich so weit wie m├Čglich in die Gedanken ├╝ber dieses Thema\nvertiefe und er├Črtere, was Herrschaft ist, welche Arten es davon gib, wie man sie\nerwirbt und erh├żlt und warum man sie verliert.\n</poem>\n\nOr, for short:\n\n\"[E]s [gibt] keine Wissenschaft ohne die Aufzeichnung dessen, was\nman begriffen hat.\"\n\n\"There is no science without a record of what one has understood\" (own translation)\n\nThat\'s why I call this Wiki system a DanteWiki.\n\n=== What does the logo show? ===\nThe logo shows a painting made \nby Michelangelo Merisi da Caravaggio in 1607. It depicts Saint Jerome\nof Stridon, who is best known for his translations of the Bible into Latin. \nit here serves as the symbol of a scientist, philosopher and thinker.\nSaint Jerome is alone, remote from the distractions of the world,\nfocused alone on putting down his thoughts.\nThe skull on his table reminds us of the mortality of man and the\nvolatility of his thoughts.\nIt thus challenges us to write down our thoughts.\n\nThe logo thus reflexts my core motives when creating this system.\n\n=== What is the relation to MediaWiki? ===\nNone.\n\nI did not want to build this system completely from scratch.\nMediaWiki was the software which contained most of the necessary \nbase functionality and was open for further development \ndue to its open license model.\nI will try to keep DanteWiki as close to MediaWiki as possible\nto ease maintenence and bug fixing.\n\n=== What is the relation to WikiPedia? ===\nNone.\n\nWhile WikiPedia is a very interesting project, I do not\nsubscribe to the objectivist perspective on which it seems\nto be grounded. In particular - in my opinion - \nthe neutral point of view goal of WikiPedia cannot be achieved\nfor a number of linguistic reasons and should not\nbe aimed for due to a number of philosophic reasons.\n\nDanteWiki follows different goals and guidelines.\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
(127,'You might want to customize the following pages:\n\n* [[Project:Privacy Information]]\n* [[Project:About]]\n* [[Project:Disclaimer]]\n* [[Project:Imprint]]\n\n\n== Copyright Customization ==\n\n<table>\n<tr><td>[[MediaWiki:Copyright]]</td><td>contains a copyright notice which is displayed in the footer of every page.</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td>[[MediaWiki:CopyrightNotice]]</td><td>contains a longer copyright notice when the user clicks on the copyright icon on the right side in the footer. It may also be linked to in other places.</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td>[[MediaWiki:Copyrightwarning]]</td><td>is displayed under the edit box when editing a page.</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td>[[MediaWiki:Copyrightwarning2]]</td><td>may be displayed in a number of places, but unfortunately the Mediawiki reference is very unclear on the details.</td></tr>\n\n</table>\n\n== Information ==\n\nThe footer may contain the following links \n\n* Privacy-link\n* About-link\n* Disclaimer-link\n* Imprint-link\n\nMore information: https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:Footer\n \n=== Privacy-Link ===\n* [[MediaWiki:Privacy]] contains the text for the privacy-link.\n* [[MediaWiki:Privacypage]] contains the name of the wiki page to which the privacy-link links to. It currently links to [[Project:Privacy]]\n\n=== About-Link ===\n* [[MediaWiki:Aboutsite]] contains the text of the about-link.\n* [[MediaWiki:Aboutpage]] contains the name of the wiki page to which the about-link links to. It currently links to [[Project:About]]\n\n=== Disclaimer-Link ===\n* [[MediaWiki:Disclaimers]] contains the text of the disclaimer-link.\n* [[MediaWiki:Disclaimerpage]] contains the name of the wiki page to which the disclaimer-link links to. it currently links to [[Project:Disclaimer]]\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
(128,'A MediaWiki has to load and compile are large number of PHP files. This takes time, so during normal operations this process usually is cached, which saves a lot of time for loading and compilation. However, during development you do not want the files to be cached but you always want the most recent changes in the source code to be used. Thus, all files have to be loaded, check and, if necessary, recompiled. Also, you might want to see warning notices about \ndeprecated functions. \n\nIn a Wikipedia installation the respective settings usually are done as part of the setup process. In DanteWiki, however, the developers want to be able to switch quickly between the different modes, so that the development cycle of DanteWiki can be faster. The setting can be switched by [[Special:Debug Mode]] and the currently active mode is displayed in the footer.\n[[Category:DanteInitialContents]]','utf-8'),
(129,'Subpages of MediaWiki:ParsifalTemplate are templates for use with Parsifal.\n\n== List of Parsifal Templates ==\n\n{{Special:PrefixIndex/MediaWiki:ParsifalTemplate/}}','utf-8'),
(130,'Subpages of MediaWiki:ParsifalTemplate are templates for use with Parsifal.\n\n== List of Parsifal Templates ==\n\n{{Special:PrefixIndex/MediaWiki:ParsifalTemplate/}}\n[[Category:ParsifalTemplate]]','utf-8'),
